# First Run Guide

Your arrstack is up. Everything below is already configured; these are just the
URLs you need and a couple of clicks to finish.

## Service URLs

{{#each services}}
- **{{name}}**: http://{{../hostIp}}:{{port}}
{{/each}}
{{#if hostnamesEnabled}}

### Hostname access (Caddy reverse proxy on :80)

Every service is also reachable at `http://<id>.{{tld}}` once the hostname
resolves to `{{hostIp}}`.

{{#if dnsmasqInstalled}}
Resolution is already handled for you on this LAN by the **dnsmasq** container
at `{{hostIp}}:53`. Point your router's DNS — or each client's `/etc/resolv.conf`
— at `{{hostIp}}` and the names below just work.
{{else}}
No LAN DNS service is installed in this stack. To use hostnames, add this one
line to the `/etc/hosts` file on every client that should reach the stack
(`sudo` required on Linux/macOS, edit as Administrator on Windows):

```
{{hostsLine}}
```
{{/if}}

Then open in a browser:

{{#each services}}
- http://{{id}}.{{../tld}}
{{/each}}
{{/if}}

## Admin Credentials

Username: **{{adminUsername}}**

The generated admin password is shared across every service and was saved to
`~/arrstack/admin.txt` at install time. To print it again later:

    arrstack show-password

## What is already done for you

- Single admin account across every service (no per-service signup)
- 8 public Prowlarr indexers added (CF-gated ones routed through FlareSolverr)
  and synced to Sonarr and Radarr
- qBittorrent download categories (tv, movies, music, books) created per TRaSH
- Sonarr/Radarr root folders and qBittorrent as download client
- Bazarr+ linked to Sonarr and Radarr, 6 subtitle providers enabled, language
  profile created from your wizard selection
- Jellyfin admin user, Movies/TV/Music libraries, and full library scan
- Jellyseerr linked to Jellyfin, Sonarr, and Radarr; libraries enabled;
  initial setup wizard skipped

## Next steps

1. Open Jellyseerr (see URL above) and sign in with the admin credentials.
2. Request a movie or TV show. The full pipeline (Prowlarr → Sonarr/Radarr →
   qBittorrent → Jellyfin) should handle the rest.
3. Optional — add credentials for two subtitle providers that need accounts.
   Open Bazarr+ **Settings → Providers** (`http://{{hostIp}}:6767/settings/providers`)
   and paste username/password for:
   - **OpenSubtitles.com** — free account at <https://www.opensubtitles.com>
   - **Addic7ed** — free account at <https://www.addic7ed.com>, strong for
     English TV releases

   The other four providers — opensubtitles (Bazarr+ web scraper for
   OpenSubtitles.org, no login needed), podnapisi, yifysubtitles, and
   embeddedsubtitles — work out of the box, so you're not blocked without
   these credentials.

If something does not work, `arrstack doctor` checks every service and prints
what is wrong.
